Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Place coconut in shallow baking pan. Bake 6 minutes, or until lightly browned, stirring after 3 minutes. Set aside. Cover large serving platter with lettuce; top with pineapple, mangoes, grapes and turkey. Beat mustard and reserved pineapple juice in small bowl with wire whisk until well blended. Drizzle over salad. Sprinkle with almonds and toasted coconut.